# ========================================
# Global .gitignore for EcoSphere Project
# ========================================

# Node.js
**/node_modules/
**/dist/
**/build/
*.log

# Environment variables (never commit secrets)
**/.env
**/.env.local
**/.env.*.local

# Multer evidence uploads (local disk storage — see backend/src/middleware/upload.ts)
# Never commit user-submitted files, and Railway's filesystem is ephemeral anyway.
backend/uploads/

# Lockfiles and migrations are intentionally NOT ignored — keep both tracked.
# A 3-person team needs matching npm installs (package-lock.json) and a
# shared source of truth for schema state (Drizzle migrations). If you
# genuinely want to stop tracking migrations later, add the line
# "**/migrations/" back in on its own — do not put the reasoning as a
# trailing comment on the same line, git will silently ignore it.

# Build outputs / caches
**/coverage/
**/.cache/
**/.temp/
**/*.tmp
**/tmp/
**/.vite/

# IDE / Editor
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Logs
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*